Rick Paxson (pax@mathworks.com) wrote:
: I am interested in buying software for PC or MAC
: to encrypt my files.  No public key just for personal
: use.  What is out there? what do you recommend? why?

: any suggestions are much appreciated

: Rick Paxson

Well, pgp -c is a good bet... SecureDrive/ SPS are good for encrypting
whole partitionson a PC... What *exactly* is the type of encryption you're
after? I would recommend using something that uses either 16 round (or
more) DES or IDEA with a random IV, but it could just be me. =)

